==English==
===Noun===
'''coryphee''', '''coryphée'''
#The [[title]] given to a [[ballet]] dancer ranking above a member of the ''[[corps de ballet]]'' and below a [[soloist]].

===Etymology===
[[w:French language|French]]; from [[w:Latin language|Latin]] ''coryphaeus'', [[w:Greek language|Greek]] ''koruphaios'', "[[leader]]"; from Greek ''koruphē'', "[[head]]".

